==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deplorable
<hw>De*plor"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧plorable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Worthy of being deplored or
lamented; lamentable; causing grief; hence, sad; calamitous; grievous;
wretched; <as>as, life's evils are deplorable</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Individual sufferers are in a much more <qex>deplorable</qex>
conditious than any others.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deplorableness</ent>⟦br⟧
